##<a id="0-8-0"></a> v0.8.0

**Release Date:** MMMM DD, 2020

### Features

New features and changes in this release:

- Filter search results by clicking on a bar in the bar chart in the Service Consumption dashboard.
- Added in-memory cache, which is disabled by default. For more information, see
<a href="installing.html#enable-cache">Enable <%= vars.product_short %> Cache</a>.

### Resolved Issues

This release has the following fixes:

- Fixed the `431 Request Header Fields Too Large` error that occurred when targeting more than four foundations.
- <%= vars.product_short %> can now target more than four foundations with more than 2,000 service instances each.
There is no maximum limit of service instances. <%= vars.product_short %> does not deny service to the Cloud Controller.<br>
<%= vars.product_short %> now limits the number of parallel requests allowed to ensure that
<%= vars.product_short %> does not deny service to the Cloud Controller.

### Known Issues

There are no known issues for this release.

